✅ 1) What is jQuery?

✅ Answer : jQuery is a fast, lightweight JavaScript library that simplifies:

DOM manipulation
event handling
animations/effects
AJAX calls
cross-browser compatibility

⭐ How to add jQuery in HTML (CDN)
<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.7.1.min.js"></script>

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- 
✅ 2) jQuery Selectors

Q2 What are jQuery selectors?
✅ Answer : Selectors are used to select HTML elements and perform actions on them.

Syntax:
$("selector")

⭐ Common selectors (Must know)

$("#id")       // select by id
$(".class")    // select by class
$("p")         // select by tag


Q3 (🔥 MMI). Difference between #id selector and .class selector?

Answer:

$("#box") selects element with id="box" (unique element)
$(".box") selects all elements with class="box" (multiple possible)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
✅ 3) DOM Manipulation & Events

Q4 What is DOM manipulation?
✅ Answer : Changing HTML content, attributes, styles dynamically using JavaScript/jQuery.

⭐ Most used DOM methods (Must learn)

1) Change text
$("#msg").text("Hello Raj");

2) Change HTML
$("#msg").html("<b>Hello</b>");

4) Add/Remove class
$("#box").addClass("active");
$("#box").removeClass("active");
$("#box").toggleClass("active");

5) CSS change
$("#box").css("background", "yellow");


Q5 Difference between .text() and .html()?
✅ Answer:

.text() → only text (tags treated as plain text)
.html() → can insert HTML tags

Example:

$("#x").text("Hello"); // shows Hello
$("#x").html("Hello"); // shows bold Hello

